# Consul fork: reduce merge friction when syncing from upstream OpenBao.
#
# go.sum is an unordered set of "module version hash" lines. Both upstream and
# this fork legitimately add lines, so a union merge (keep both sides' hunks)
# virtually eliminates go.sum conflicts. Any stray/duplicate line is cleaned up
# by the mandatory `go mod tidy` run after every upstream merge.
#
# NOTE: do NOT union-merge go.mod — it is section-sensitive and a union merge can
# produce an invalid file. go.mod conflicts are resolved by `go mod tidy`.
go.sum merge=union
